                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.79620 Boeing Airplane Co./2: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgam</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="96" xml:id="d662fn96">The same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis
                            mutandis</hi>, on the same date to the missions in Argentina (No. 6),
                        Chile (No. 14), Peru (No. 9), and Uruguay (No. 2).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-02-06T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 6, 1928—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3. Captain Ralph A. O’Neill, representing the Boeing Airplane Company of Seattle,
                    and the Pratt and Whitney Motor Corporation of Hartford, Connecticut, is sailing
                    on S. S. <hi rend="italic">Southern Cross</hi> February 11, for Rio de Janeiro
                    for an experimental flight and to demonstrate before army and navy air
                    service.</p>
                <p>Please request free entry for equipment, including Boeing pursuit plane, Boeing
                    mail plane and accessories, and ask permission for flight in Brazil. Reply by
                    cable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Olds</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
